Lets assume we're releasing version 6.2

* Update the source tree

   svn update .

* Check that nothing's dangling

   svn status -u

* Update the version in src/setup.py
    ...
    'version'          : '6.2',
    ...

* commit

    svn commit -m "updated version"

* TODO: create release notes
* TODO: create a changelog

* Branch the release:

  svn copy https://opensvn.csie.org/testoob/trunk https://opensvn.csie.org/testoob/branches/RB-6.2

* Create the distfile

  make dist

* Upload the distfile to SourceForge

  ncftpput distfile.tar.gz ftp://upload.sourceforge.net/incoming

* Create a SourceForge release
  (Admin -> File Releases -> Add Release)
  Or directly:
  http://sourceforge.net/project/admin/newrelease.php?package_id=152827&group_id=138557

  Call the release '6.2', choose the distfile

* Download the release, see that it works

* Update some news file somewhere (where?)

* Update PyPi:

  python src/setup.py register

* Celebrate
